# Cline Rules for GoodWorkflows

## Session Start Protocol
- On every new session, read all files in `memory-bank/` to regain project context:
  - `project-brief.md` — What this repo is and who it's for
  - `architecture.md` — DSL2 module graph, workflow composition, config layering
  - `tech-stack.md` — Technologies, containers, libraries in use
  - `conventions.md` — Naming, patterns, error handling rules
  - `workflows.md` — Detailed breakdown of each saved workflow
  - `modules.md` — Catalog of all DSL2 processes with I/O specs
  - `configs.md` — All config profiles with parameter tables
  - `ci-cd.md` — CI pipeline, smoke tests, docs deploy
  - `session-notes.md` — What was done in previous sessions

## Session End Protocol
- Append a dated entry to `memory-bank/session-notes.md` summarizing:
  - What was changed and why
  - Any architectural decisions made
  - Any memory bank files that need updating to stay in sync

## Project-Specific Rules

### Never Edit Generated Files
- `site/` — MkDocs build output
- `.nextflow/` — Nextflow cache
- `work/` — Nextflow work directory
- `outputs/` — Published pipeline results
- `logs/` — Nextflow reports and SLURM logs
- `test-results/` — CI test artifacts
- `.ci/docker-cache/` — CI container cache

### Code Conventions (see conventions.md for full details)
- Process names: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Workflow names: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Module directories: `snake_case`
- Workflow files: `snake_case.nf`
- Config files: `lowercase.config`
- Shell scripts: `snake_case.sh`
- Documentation: `kebab-case.md`

### Every Process MUST Have a Stub Block
- Stub blocks create expected output files (even if empty/touch)
- This enables `-stub-run` for CI smoke tests

### Channel Patterns
- Per-sample: `tuple val(meta), path(file)` where meta has `id`, `output_file_id`, `species`
- Aggregation: Use `.collect()` before passing to multi-input processes

### Sensitive Values
- Never hardcode credentials in params
- LabKey auth via `.netrc` mounted read-only into containers

### Config Layering
- `base.config` → profile config (local/slurm/slurm_singularity/test)
- Never duplicate params between base and profile configs

### When Adding a New Module
1. Create `modules/local/<category>/<name>/main.nf`
2. Add `stub:` block
3. Add process label
4. Add resource specs to relevant config profiles
5. Update `memory-bank/modules.md`
6. Add module smoke test in `tests/modules/`

### When Adding a New Workflow
1. Create `workflows/<name>.nf`
2. Include required modules
3. Add to `main.nf` switch block
4. Add to supported workflows list
5. Update `memory-bank/workflows.md`
6. Add workflow smoke test to CI